# 1. Automatically handle newline characters (crucial for cross-platform Python script execution)
* text=auto

# 2. Explicitly define Python scripts as text files and force the use of LF newlines (compliant with Linux/server standards)
*.py text eol=lf

# 3. Explicitly specify that the dataset archive is a binary file and perform no text conversion
*.zip binary

# 4. If you plan to use LFS to track these zip files later (currently, web uploads can be left unenabled, but it is recommended to keep this as a backup)
# *.zip filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# 5. Ensure that README and other documents display correctly on all platforms
*.md text
*.txt text
